Preconditions:
- The input array `costs` is not null.
- The length of the input array `costs` is even.
- The length of the input array `costs` is at least 2 and at most 100.
- The values of `aCosti` and `bCosti` in each element of the input array `costs` are between 1 and 1000 (inclusive).

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum cost to fly every person to a city.
- Exactly `n` people arrive in each city, where `n` is half the length of the input array `costs`.
- The total minimum cost is calculated by summing the costs of flying each person to their respective cities.